# Community Library Product Context

- Build for two zones: public community content and authenticated library access.
- Keep library PDFs restricted to registered users only.
- Never expose direct public file URLs for protected PDFs.
- Enforce authorization in backend policies/middleware, not only UI checks.
- Prefer signed/temporary download links with access checks and expiry.
- Track download activity for auditing and abuse monitoring.
- Make all user-facing content clear: public article vs members-only library resource.
- Keep accessibility and mobile responsiveness as baseline requirements.
- Optimize for maintainability: clear service boundaries, tests, and documented decisions.
